body:
I have a weird error message when checking my session handling with psalm:

```
ERROR: UnusedFunctionCall - public/initialize.php:176:1 - The call to session_start is not used
session_start(
```

is thrown on the following code:

```
ini_set('session.cookie_secure', '1');
ini_set('session.cookie_httponly', '1');
require_once(Constants::getString('ROOTDIR') . '/vendor/adodb/adodb-php/session/adodb-session2.php');
require_once(Constants::getString('ROOTDIR') . '/vendor/adodb/adodb-php/session/adodb-encrypt-md5.php');
require_once(Constants::getString('ROOTDIR') . '/vendor/adodb/adodb-php/session/adodb-encrypt-sha1.php');
ADOdb_Session::config(
    Config::getString('dbtype'),
    Config::getString('dbhost'),
    Config::getString('dbuser'),
    Config::getString('dbpass'),
    Config::getString('dbname'),
    ['table' => 'sessions'],
    );
ADOdb_Session::persist(false);
ADODB_Session::filter(new ADODB_Encrypt_SHA1());
ADODB_Session::filter(new ADODB_Encrypt_MD5());
session_start(
    [
        'cookie_httponly' => true,
        'cookie_secure'   => true,
        'gc_maxlifetime' => (60 * 60 * 24),
        'cookie_lifetime' => (60 * 60),
        'name'            => 'bookasession',
        'use_strict_mode' => true,
    ]
);
```

ADOdb Sessions are documented here: http://adodb.org/dokuwiki/doku.php?id=v5:session:session_index

I am not sure what to make of the "unused function call" error. The session is started, ADODB is putting the session into the database. All seems to be well and I am pretty sure `session_start()` is running and doing _something_. Why would session_start() not being "used"?

ADODb is here: https://github.com/ADOdb/ADOdb

I am aware that the code of ADODb is "horribly" documented in sense of PHPDoc comments (wrong use of phpdoc at many places). Maybe that is irritating psalm?
